<HEADLINE> Largest Number of Adult Illiterates in India: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- India has the largest number of
adult illiterate population and maximum number of children are
deprived of their primary schooling, said a report here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report on South Asia human development for 1998, released
here by former Indian prime minister Inder Kumar Gujral, however,
sounded optimistic, saying that this state of educational
deprivation could be reversed if a fresh approach was taken to
educational priorities and policies.
</P>
<P>
The report said that one in three children in India drops out
before completing the primary cycle and one in two children does
not have access to clean drinking water at school.
</P>
<P>
Turning to the whole area in the subcontinent, the report said
that South Asia will face a catastrophe if drastic actions are not
taken to achieve universalisation of basic education in the next
five years. The region has slipped behind all other regions of the
world including sub Sahara in human development levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
