<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, April 4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kampala-- Fresh outbreak of cholera has claimed 83 lives in
eastern Uganda, the New Vision reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Richard Othieno, the Mbale District
Director of Health Services, as blaming a religious sect for
blocking timely medical assistance from health institutions.
(Uganda-cholera)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The second Asia-Europe meeting closed here Saturday
with the adoption of a chairman's statement.
</P>
<P>
The two-day conference, participated by the leaders of 10 Asian
countries and EU's 15 member states plus president of the EU
commission, covered a wide range of political, economic and social
issues.
</P>
<P>
The leaders also agreed to set up an ASEM Trust Fund to provide
assistance to Asian countries, primarily in assessing the poverty
impact of the financial crisis. (ASEM2-Conclusion)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Another batch of about 1,000 Iraqi prisoners of war
(POWs) released by Iran have returned to their homeland, the Iraqi
News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said Iraq again set free 50 Iranians captured during
their eight-year war from 1980-88 in the latest POW exchange, a
decade after the fightings ended. (Iraq-Iran-POWs)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- No fewer than 280 passengers were feared dead in a
boat accident in Akwa Ibom state, southeastern Nigeria, the Daily
Times reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The boat was said to have been rocked by violent waves in the
course of its voyage and capsized near a beach Wednesday.
(Nigeria-boat accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The 25 leaders attending the second Asia-Europe
Meeting (ASEM 2) agreed on Saturday to foster political dialogue,
reinforce cooperation in economic and other fields.
</P>
<P>
By adopting the Chairman's Statement at the end of the two-day
conference, leaders confirmed that the ASEM process should be
conducted on the basis of equal partnership, mutual respect and
mutual benefit. (ASEM-Statement) 
</P>
