<HEADLINE> China to Send More Medical Teams to Madagascar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANTANANARIVO, Madagascar, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China has agreed
to send more medical teams to Madagascar to help with the
country's medical service.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Ma Zhixue and Madagascar's Health Minister
Henriette Rahantalalao signed an agreement to the effect on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese ambassador said at the signing ceremony that China
has dispatched 11 batches of medical teams to the African country
since 1975. 
</P>
