<HEADLINE> Search Continuing for Missing Plane: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Searchers are still looking for
debris from a small plane that crashed in Lake Pontchartrain in
New Orleans of the United States late Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Coast Guard Lieutenant Matthew McGlynn said Saturday that two
boats are using sonar to scan the lake bottom about five meters
below in the area where the plane presumably went down, United
Press International reported.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft was flying from Denton, Texas, to New Orleans when
it vanished from radar about 16 kilometers north of New Orleans
Lakefront Airport.
</P>
<P>
One woman was recovered Friday, but three people are still
missing.
</P>
<P>
Carmen Rivera-Worley, 44, of Denton survived by clinging to
floating wreckage from the single-engine Piper aircraft for at
least 10 hours.
</P>
<P>
Coast Guard Petty Officer Kristi Lutrell said the others still
missing are Rivera-Worley's daughter, the pilot and a passenger.
</P>
</TEXT>
