<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: ASEM2 Summit Ends with Achievements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addressing the final press conference after the two-day
meeting, British Prime Minister Tony Blair said that ASEM2's
achievements on Asian financial crisis "means the success of the
Second Asia-Europe Meeting."
</P>
<P>
Leaders from 25 ASEM countries and the EU Commission adopted a
special statement on the financial difficulties in Asia Friday
evening, highlighting their determination to tackle the financial
crisis in some Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the statement, all the participants expressed confidence
that with full implementation of the necessary policy reforms and
strong mutual support, financial stability in Asia would be
restored.
</P>
<P>
"Strong economic fundamentals would enable Asia's impressive
growth performance to continue over the medium term," the
statement said, stressing "Europe's deep interest in the
resolution of Asia's financial difficulties."
</P>
<P>
In an effort to provide concrete assistance to some affected
Asian countries, the Chairman's statement issued at the end of the
ASEM conference said that ASEM leaders agreed to set up an ASEM
Trust Fund at the World Bank and the Center for Financial
Restructuring to provide valuable technical assistance to some
Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji, who reaffirmed China's
determination not to devaluate the Chinese currency, was widely
praised by many participating ASEM leaders. The Chinese initiative
of holding a conference of ASEM Science and Technology ministers
was also widely discussed at this conference.
</P>
<P>
Economic and trade cooperation between the two regions is
another major focus of the ASEM2 conference. The Trade
Facilitation Action Plan and the Investment Promotion Action Plan,
formally adopted at this conference, are expected to give a fresh
impetus to further economic and trade cooperation between Asia and
Europe in the future.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the ASEM leaders also pledged to enhance
cooperation and coordination on the environmental, international
crimes and other global issues. An Asia-Europe Environmental
Technology Center will be established in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Satisfied with the results of the conference, Prime Minister
Blair said that the achievements of ASEM2 show that "we are
building a new partnership between Europe and Asia for the next
century." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
