<P>
Former Iranian president Ali Akbar Rafsanjani paid a two-week
visit to the kingdom starting from February 21, during which he
held wide-scale talks with King Fahd on boosting bilateral ties
and other issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
During Rafsanjani's visit, the two countries agreed to set up a
joint committee aimed at looking into means to upgrade bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two largest oil producers in the Gulf,
strained following Iran's Islamic revolution in 1979, have been
warming up since last year when Iran started to make initiatives
to reconciliate with the Gulf Arab neighbors. 
