<HEADLINE> Palestinian Security Service Accused of Killing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 5 (Xinhua) -- A leader of the radical Islamic
group Hamas Sunday accused the Palestinian Preventive Security
Service (PSS) of killing Hamas' leading activist Muhi Sharif,
Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Hamas leader in Gaza Abdel Aziz Rantisi was quoted by the radio
as saying that the PSS has arrested Sharif, tortured him to death
and dumped his body in a booby-trapped car before detonating it in
the West Bank city of Ramallah.
</P>
<P>
Rantisi said that during the questioning, Sharif may have
confessed or given the names of contacts to Palestinian security
officials, who he said started rounding up Hamas activists after
the incident.
</P>
<P>
The body of Sharif, who was suspected of being Hamas' main
bombmaker and masterminding several suicide bombing attacks in
Israel, was found last Sunday in an explosive-rigged car detonated
by a remote control.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian security officials have hinted that Israel was
involved in the killing. But Israel has categorically denied the
charge.
</P>
<P>
Rantisi said that Hamas is investigating the case.
</P>
<P>
He called on the Izzadin Kassam, Hamas' military wing, to
continue its struggle against Israel.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian officials were quoted by Israel Radio as saying
that Hamas has rejected a request by the Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) that the group refrain from carrying out attacks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ami Ayalon, head of Israeli General Security
Service, Sunday briefed the Israeli cabinet on the situation in
the Palestinian self-rule areas after the death of Sharif and the
steps which have been taken by the Israeli security forces to
prevent terror attacks. 
</P>
