<HEADLINE> Woman Killed in Kampala Blasts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kampala, April 5 (Xinhua) -- One woman was killed and 10
others were wounded Saturday night in Kampala in two separate
blasts, witnesses and police sources told Xinhua Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The victim was a waitress, and the injured, including three
Burundi nationals, three Ugandans and a Kenyan have been sent to
local Mulago Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The blasts were caused by hand grenades thrown into a hotel at
09:30 p.m. and into Nile Grill near Uganda House two hours later
in central Kampala.
</P>
<P>
Nobody claimed responsibility for the attacks for the time
being but some local people said they might be terrorist
activities of anti-government rebels.
</P>
<P>
There are two main rebel groups in the country: the Lord's
Resistance Army (LRA) acting in the north and the Allied
Democratic Forces (ADF) operating in the west.
</P>
<P>
Everything is going normally in the city Sunday. But local
business community said the blasts may have serious influence on
the business confidence in the country.
</P>
<P>
John Kisembo, the police deputy inspector general, was robbed
of a cellular phone, a watch and other things including a pistol
in Hotel Africana in the city Tuesday, the official New Vision
paper reported Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
