<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rats Cut Off Telecommunication Lines in C. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The telecommunication lines
between Uganda and its neighbors including Burundi, Rwanda and
Tanzania have been cut off by rat gnawing, "The New Vision" paper
reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The cables at Nkasi telecommunication repeater station
amplifying signals in Central Mpigi District have been nibbled by
the rodents, experts determined Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The station was established in the eighties. Most of its six
kilometers-long lines is very bushy and need constant
maintenance. But the last inspection was held 18 months ago. Such
equipment in the station needs routine check, experts said.
</P>
<P>
The telecommunication link between the center and the west of
the country has also been damaged, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Uganda Telecommunication limited has sent its specialists to
repair the cables and equipment in the station. 
</P>
</TEXT>
