<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest China Region to Protect Overseas Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- "Overseas-funded enterprises have
the right to refuse any unlawful levies," Ma Qizhi, acting
chairman of the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region's government,
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Ma made the announcement at a working conference on opening
the region's economy wider to the outside world. He also said that
government departments and individuals may not check on the
work in overseas-funded enterprises without the appropriate
permission.
</P>
<P>
The land-locked region in northwest China has made remarkable
progress in improving its investment environment during the past
few years, he said. However, problems remain that need to be
addressed, including illicit levies and interference with the
decision-making power of overseas-funded businesses under the
pretext of enhancing management.
</P>
<P>
To tackle the problem, Ma said the items and the prices of the
lawful levies will be announced to the public in accordance with
state regulations.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a leading group for further opening-up headed by
senior local officials will soon be set up to discuss and solve
problems. Service and complaint centers should be established by
governments at the regional, city and prefectural levels as soon
as possible to safeguard the legal rights of overseas-funded
enterprises, Ma said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
