<HEADLINE> Ramos to Leave for Official Visit to United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
will leave Monday for a four-day official visit to the United
States "to strengthen Philippine-American partnership."
</P>
<P>
Ramos, who will be accompanied by a small group of Cabinet
members, will leave Manila for Los Angeles on board Philippine
Airlines flight PR102, the Presidential Office said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He will stop by New York on his way to Washington for a one-day
stop-over to bring the message of the country's "basic stability,
continuing economic viability and excellent prospects for
business, trade and investments despite the ongoing regional
currency crisis," the office said.
</P>
<P>
