<HEADLINE> EU to Send Mission to Help Asian Economies Recover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
send a mission to Asian countries including Malaysia in an effort
to help Asian economies recover, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The EU mission, which will come at the earliest possible time,
would explore investment opportunities in Asia, among other
things, Mahathir told reporters at the Kuala Lumpur International
Airport upon returning from the second Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM
2) in London.
</P>
<P>
"The emphasis of the mission is that it is a non fact-finding
one because if it is a fact-finding mission they may find facts
which could discourage them from investing here. Instead it is a
mission to help towards economic recovery through investment and
the like," Mahathir told an airport press conference.
</P>
<P>
The sending of the mission, mooted by South Korea, was one of
the decisions at the three-day ASEM 2, which was attended by the
leaders of the 15 EU members and 10 Asian countries, Mahathir
said, adding although the proposal for the mission came from South
Korea, the meeting agreed that it should cover all Asian states.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said he was convinced that the EU had not only
understood the current economic situation in Asia but were also
keen in cooperating with countries in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
