<HEADLINE> Sampras Pulls out of Hong Kong Open Citing Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras, whose reign as
world number one ended after 102 consecutive weeks last week when
Chilean Marcelo Rios took over, has withdrawn from this week's
Hong Kong Open due to injury, organisers said here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
His compatriot and defending Hong Kong Open champion Michael
Chang would take his place to appear at the opening ceremony, the
organisers said.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, a former Wimbledon, Australian and U.S. Open champion,
has had a poor year by his own high standards.
</P>
<P>
He had won just one title in five tournaments this year and was
beaten in the third round of the Lipton championships two weeks
ago by 36th-ranked Wayne Ferreira of South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
