<HEADLINE> Demet Wins Tour de Snowy Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- American Dede Demet held off
Australia's Anna Wilson to win the inaugural Tour De Snowy women's
cycling five-day race here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old from Colorado beat Wilson by two minutes 37
seconds with 12-time world champion Jeannie Longo-Ciprelli of
France third with 12 minutes 23 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Wilson won the first of two Sunday stages in the 13-kilometer
time trial finishing five seconds clear of 1996 world champion
Clara Hughes of Canada with Longo-Ciprelli a further seven seconds
away in third.
</P>
<P>
In the final stage, a 30km criterium around Canberra's London
Circuit, Demet's teammate Karen Livingstone won from fellow
American Kendra Wenzel and 1992 Olympic gold medallist Petra
Rossner of Germany third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
