<HEADLINE> Japan Beat New Zealand 3-2 in Davis Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Japan's national champion Takao
Suzuki clinched the final match by beating New Zealand 3-2 in
Miyazaki, Japan, on Sunday to secure a place in the playoff for
joining the Davis Cup tennis World Group.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old, who pulled off a big upset win over ace Brett
Steven on Friday, beat Teo Susnjak 6-4, 6-7 (5-7), 6-4, 6-1, to
win the Asia Oceania zone Group One second round tie.
</P>
<P>
The third set went with serves till Suzuki won a deuce to score
the only break of the set and he chalked up a 4-0 lead over a
disappointed Susnjak in the fourth set before closing the
183-minute match.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, New Zealand tied the contest when Steven, determined
to restore pride after a three-set loss on Friday, came back from
one set down twice to beat Toichi Motomura 3-6, 6-2, 3-6, 6-3, 6-4
in three hours two minutes.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time Japan has defeated New Zealand, thanks
largely to the specially-built slow clay court surface here. Japan
have lost the previous three encounters in 1979, 1993 and 1994.
</P>
</TEXT>
