<HEADLINE> Chinese Pay Tribute to Legendary Ancestors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of people from all
walks of life in the city of Baoji today participated in
activities to commemorate Yan Di, one of two legendary ancestors
of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Baoji, in northwest China's Shaanxi Province, is believed to be
the native place of Yan Di, also known as Shennong, and April 5
each year is the Chinese Qingming Festival, an occasion for people
to visit ancestral graves.
</P>
<P>
Yan Di and Huang Di, who also was known as the Yellow Emperor,
are believed to be the ancestors of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
In a similar development, 10,000 Chinese from home and abroad
today gathered at the site of the tomb of Huang Di for a memorial
ceremony for their ancient ancestor.
</P>
<P>
Among the people who attended the ceremony were Jiang Zhenghua,
vice chairman of the National People's Congress Standing
Committee, and Wang Zhaoguo, vice chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of central government departments, provinces
and municipalities, the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
and Macao -- joined by Taiwan compatriots and representatives of
overseas Chinese -- presented baskets of flowers at the Huang Di
tomb.  
</P>
</TEXT>
