<HEADLINE> Kenyan Jackson Kabiga Wins Paris Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's Jackson Kabiga won the 22nd
Paris Marathon on Sunday in two hours, nine minutes and 36 seconds
while Australia's Nicole Caroll won the women's race.
</P>
<P>
Kabiga beat the meet record for the Paris Marathon that was set
in 1992 by Luis Soares of France with a time of two hours, ten
minutes and three seconds.
</P>
<P>
Caroll also broke the previous time for women in the Paris
Marathon, running the race in two hours, 27 minutes and six
seconds.
</P>
<P>
The earlier record had been held by Mari Tanigawa of Japan, who
won in 1994 with a time of two hours, 27 minutes and 55 seconds.
</P>
</TEXT>
