<HEADLINE> China-U.S. Law Seminar to Feature Anti-Dumping Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The ninth China-U.S. law seminar,
which will be organized by the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), will focus on anti-dumping issues,
according to the International Business Daily.
</P>
<P>
The two-day seminar opens Tuesday. It will cover procedural
issues between China and the United States, including progress in
anti-dumping legislation, its appraisal, the legal process of
investigations and responses to lawsuits.
</P>
<P>
The seminar also will include arbitration issues between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is an exchange program sponsored by MOFTEC and the
U.S. Department of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
Expected to attend the seminar are representatives from China's
Supreme People's Court, MOFTEC, the China Arbitration Committee
for International Trade, the U.S. Commerce Department, business
people and lawyers.  
