<HEADLINE> Chinese Entrepreneur Brushes Up Toothpaste Success Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Private entrepreneur Hu Zegang has
become a dominant player in China's toothpaste sector, as his
factory provides more than half of the calcite powder for the
country's toothpaste producers.
</P>
<P>
His calcite powder-processing factory turned over 1.03 million
yuan in taxes to the state last year, and he was awarded a prize
by the National Council for Light Industry for his outstanding
contribution to China's toothpaste industrial and technological
progress.
</P>
<P>
Hu started his business in Lingchuan County of Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region in 1983. Leaving his post in a local mining
machinery plant, he raised 500 yuan to start processing calcite
powder, an important raw material for toothpaste industry.
</P>
<P>
He was sure that he would make a career in this field because
he found great potential in a 1.2-billion-people consumption
market.
</P>
<P>
Now his business, with more than 10 million yuan in fixed
assets, processes 55,000 tons of high-quality calcite powder
annually.
</P>
<P>
Last year, he presided over the drafting of the country's first
standards for toothpaste powder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
