Israeli police were injured in violent clashes that erupted
Saturday night in northern Arab village of Sued, Israel Radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
Beduin Arab residents, in their hundreds, threw stones at
Israeli police when they were prevented from demolishing three
settlement buildings built without licenses from Israeli
authorities.
</P>
<P>
Police used tear gas and batons to disperse the rioters, and a
police helicopter was called in to end the melee, which lasted
till the wee hours of Sunday. Order was restored in the morning
and roads to the village were reopened.
</P>
