Olympic gold medallist over the distance, and Britain's Paula
Radcliffe, the world cross country eight-km silver medallist two
weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Radcliffe led the pace and looked strong throughout the race.
However, the Portuguese reserved more strength to reel over her in
the final lap and crossed the line in 30:48.06. Radcliffe was
second in a British record of 30:48.58. 
</P>
