TOKYO, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Max Biaggi shot to an
easy win in the season-opening Japan Grand Prix in Suzuka, on
Sunday while reigning champ Michael Doohan did not finish the
500cc motorcycling race.
</P>
<P>
According to Reuter's report, Biaggi on Honda had the lead from
pole to finish and outrun by about five seconds teammates Tadayuki
Okada and Noriyuki Namba on Yamaha, both from Japan.
