<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Plans to Set up Two More EPZs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government plans to
set up two export processing zones (EPZs) in the southwest and
southeast of the country to meet growing demands for investment in
the EPZs.
</P>
<P>
The two planned EPZs expected to cost a total of 1.3 billion
taka (28.26 million U.S. dollars) will be located in Mongla and
Comilla, 170 km and 90 km southwest and southeast of here
respectively, media reports said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina is expected to lay the foundation
stone of Mongla EPZ in the first week of next month and Comilla in
the last week of May, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 166 and 63 hectares of land has already been
acquired for Mongla and Comilla EPZs respectively.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are only two EPZs -- Dhaka and Chittagong --
in this South Asian country. The two EPZs are developing fast, but
they can not meet domestic and foreign investors' demands.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
