<HEADLINE> Kwan Wins Crown at Figure Skating Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MINNEAPOLIS, Minnesota, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Michelle Kwan of
the United States won the lady's gold medal at the World Figure
Skating Championships at the Target Center here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kwan, silver medalist at the Winter Olympic Games in Nagano,
Japan earlier this year, performed steadily to the tune of the
music but fell in a triple jump, like all the other last
competitors who fell one another in their efforts for the medals.
</P>
<P>
"Those are the mistakes I don't usually make. I was very
surprised. I think I took it a little easy on the triple salchow,
but I managed to pull off the end of the program, which I am proud
of," the 17-year-old said afterwards,
</P>
<P>
Kwan, who also won the title in 1996, was awarded all 5.7s for
technical performace and almost all 5.9 marks for presentation.
</P>
<P>
She won the world title this time with reigning Olympic
gold medalist Tara Lipinski of the United States and bronze
medalist Chen Lu of China missing.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Irina Slutskaya, who was placed fifth at Nagano and
bronze medalist at 1996 World Championships, pocketed the
silver medal.
</P>
<P>
Maria Butyrskaya, also a Russian who was fourth placer at the
Olympics this year, finished third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
