<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Focuses on Housing for Local, Hong Kong Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Real estate investment in the
Shenzhen Special Economic Zone is estimated at 13.6 billion yuan
(1.638 billion U.S. dollars) this year, with the focus on
providing housing to local and Hong Kong residents.
</P>
<P>
Under the yearly plan, 1.61 billion yuan will be used for the
construction of 9,028 low-cost flats.
</P>
<P>
The land supply allocated for this year is 10.393 million
square meters, a drop of 33.7 percent from last year. Of that
total 1.16 million square meters, or 11 percent, will be used for
housing construction.
</P>
<P>
The control in land supply is conducive to boosting the market,
local officials said.
</P>
<P>
The housing scheme is also expected to benefit low-income Hong
Kong buyers who are ready to buy a home in Shenzhen. 
</P>
