<HEADLINE> Paris St Germain Wins French League Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Paris St Germain won the French
League Cup on Sunday by beating Girondins Bordeaux on penalties
following their 2-2 draw after extra time here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian defender Paulo Gralak and veteran striker Jean-Pierre
Papin missed Bordeaux's first two penalties in the shootout while
Paris St Germain converted all theirs.
</P>
<P>
Johan Micoud put the Girondins ahead just after the half hour
but Marco Simone equalised 10 minutes from time for the Paris side.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Rai put Paris St Germain ahead for the first time on
a header 17 minutes into the extra time.
</P>
<P>
Papin hit a fine equaliser when he curled a free kick near the
edge of the box over the wall and into the corner of the net for
his fifth goal of the competition. 
</P>
