<HEADLINE> Seles Ousted at Family Circle Cup Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Third-seeded American Monica
Seles was ousted by the 9th seed Irina Spirlea of Romania 4-6,
6-1, 6-7 (5-7) in the semifinals of the Family Circle Cup women's
tennis tourney on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
After winning the second set 6-1, Seles rallied from a 4-1
deficit in the final set and held leads of 5-4 and 6-5 but could
not put Spirlea away.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian then battled back twice as Seles served for the
match to force the tie-break.
</P>
<P>
The match, played in Hilton Head Island in South Carolina,
lasted more than two hours.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's final, Spirlea will meet fourth seed Amanda
Coezter, who won two matches Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The South African beat American Lisa Raymond 6-4, 6-1 in the
semifinals after a quarter-final win over German Andrea Glass, who
retired trailing 4-6, 7-6 (7-2) due to a strained abdominal
muscle. 
</P>
