<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Rises by 187 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market spurted the 4,000-mark
psychological barrier for the first time this year during the
week.
</P>
<P>
The sensitive index on BSE market during the week rose
gradually on day-to-day buying and closed at 4,095.60 as against
last week's close of 3,908.60.
</P>
<P>
The national index also ended higher at 1,770.40 from 1,702.73.
The BSE-200 and US dollar index were quoted higher at 392.00 and
165.18 compared with last week's close of 378.03 and 159.34
respectively.
</P>
<P>
A jubilant mood prevailed on BSE market during the week
following the assurance from new Finance Minister Yashwant Sinha
that the BJP-led coalition government would seek to maintain an
orderly foreign exchange market, and the slashing of interest
rates by the Reserve Bank of India. 
</P>
