<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Buy More Helicopter Gunships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Air Force (SLAF)
plans to buy more Mi-24 helicopter gunships to strengthen its
fleet of attack helicopters, The official Sunday Observer
newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A Defense Ministry team has just returned from Ukraine and the
SLAF hopes to take delivery of at least two or four Mi-24
helicopters shortly, the report quoted an Air Force Spokesman as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the machines are being acquired on a
government-to-government basis.
</P>
<P>
The SLAF already operates a small fleet of Mi-24 helicopter
gunships, acquired from the former Soviet Union, in its No. 9
Attack Helicopter Squadron based at Hingurakgoda in North Central
Province.
</P>
<P>
The military has acquired modern weapons systems in recent
years and wants to build up their numbers to provide fire support
to army troops during operations against the Tamil rebels who have
been fighting a war against the Sri Lankan government for a
separate state in the north and east of the country since 1983.
</P>
