<HEADLINE> Presidents of Andean Community Meet in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of the five Andean Community
nations will meet Sunday in Ecuador's largest industrial city of
Guayaquil on regional integration, economic growth and a future
common market.
</P>
<P>
At the Andean Community Summit, the 10th of the kind,
presidents of Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru and Venezuela will
also coordinate their trade policies and apply unified tariffs.
</P>
<P>
Opening the session, Ecuador's Acting President Fabian Alarcon
said the Andean Community economy has been growing fast in recent
years, and internal trade has been up 20 percent on annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Alarcon expected the total export of the group could exceed 6.8
billion U.S. dollars this year.
</P>
<P>
The bloc, he said, would shore up trade links with South
America's largest trade bloc Mercosur, the European Union (EU),
the Caribbean countries and the Asian-Pacific nations.
</P>
<P>
Also joining the two-day meeting as an observer was President
Ernesto Perez of Panama, which is trying to gain entry into the
group as its sixth member. 
</P>
