<DOCNO> XIE19980405.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombian Coffee Price Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Colombian coffee's
internal purchasing price will be down 1.85 percent Saturday to
start at 331,375 pesos (about 255 U.S. dollars) per 125-kilogram
bag.
</P>
<P>
The internal price is based on the lowest quote of last three
days, as an imminent downward trend is observed in the price
diminishing on daily basis in the first three days of the month.
</P>
<P>
Colombian coffee closed Friday at 1.59 dollars per pound (about
0.45 kilogram) at the international market.
</P>
<P>
The sluggish market development has caused big concerns among
Colombian coffee growers, who met last week at the Coffee Union to
analyze and formulate a strategy.
</P>
<P>
However, at the meeting, they signaled their disagreements with
the formula for the determination of prices, applied by the
Colombian Coffee Growers Federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
