<HEADLINE> Britain Offers Scholarship for Thai Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Britain has offered scholarships
for Thai students currently studying or planning to go to the
United Kingdom, Sunday's Bangkok Post reported.
</P>
<P>
The offer was made by British Prime Minister Tony Blair to his
Thai counterpart Chuan Leekpai during their meeting in London on
the sidelines of the second Asia-Europe summit.
</P>
<P>
During the summit, Thailand and Britain signed a "Thailand-UK
Action Agenda" which pledges wide-ranging cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The size of the scholarships had not been decided and the
British government would discuss with universities and the private
sector regarding the pledge, the paper quoted Thai government
spokesman Akkapol Sorasuchart as saying.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Thai students are studying in Britain, many of
them facing financial difficulty due to the baht's depreciation
against the pound, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
About 600-700 students had been selected to further their
studies in Britain under the Thai government scholarship but they
were unable to go due to the shortage of government funds, Thai
Foreign Minister Surin Pitsuwan said.
</P>
<P>
The government would start selecting students to study under
Britain's offer after the Thai delegation returned to Bangkok, he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
