<HEADLINE> Romania Takes Unbeatable Lead over Norway in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Romania took an unbeatable 3-0
lead over Norway in the Davis Cup tennis Euro/African zone Group
One tie after winning the doubles here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Gabriel Trifu paired with Andrei Pavel to defeat Norway's Lars
Hjarrand and Helge Koll 6-3, 6-2 and 6-2 to seal the Romanian
victory.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Dinu Pescariu, who was ranked 86th in the world,
beat Jan Frode Andersen 7-6, 6-4 and 6-4 in the opening singles
rubber.
</P>
<P>
The 92nd-ranked Pavel then continued the momentum to dispose
of Christian Ruud 6-2, 6-2 and 6-2 in another rubber on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The reverse singles will be played on Sunday but would be
meaningless as Romania has secured the winning position.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that the two teams met in the Davis Cup
since Romania beat Norway 5-0 in Oslo in 1986. 
</P>
