<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand, Laos Agree on Site of Second Border Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and Laos have agreed on
the construction site for a second Thai-Laos border bridge, the
Bangkok Post said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted an official from the Communications
Ministry as saying the agreement was reached last month as part of
the two countries' efforts to enhance trade and to bring
prosperity to the border area.
</P>
<P>
Thailand and Laos will share equally the estimated 1.4
billion-baht (35 million U.S. dollars) construction cost.
</P>
<P>
Japan has already offered a 700-million-baht (17.5 million
dollar) soft loan to Thailand with a 2.7 percent interest rate to
be repaid over 25 years with a grace period of seven years.
</P>
<P>
Laos will receive a 30-year soft loan at one percent interest
with a 10-year grace period.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is expected to be finished in three years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
