<DOCNO> XIE19980405.0143 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Township Enterprises Improving Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Township enterprises in
Guangzhou, the capital of China's Guangdong Province, exported
more than 26 billion yuan worth of goods last year, a 22.25
percent rise from 1996.
</P>
<P>
Companies in Panyu, a city under Guangzhou's administration
accounted for 51 percent of that, and Guangzhou now has 12
township enterprises with export licenses.
</P>
<P>
Township companies got more than 8.2 billion yuan in overseas
funds last year, up 66 percent from 1996, and accounting for
nearly 40 percent of their total capital.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
