<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Backs EU Efforts to Help Palestine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Italy will back the European Union
(EU) in the regional bloc's efforts to help the Palestinians, a
Foreign Ministry statement said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The statement said Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini told his
Egyptian counterpart Amr Moussa that as an EU member, Italy will
provide aid for Palestinians' economic reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
Dini, who met Moussa here Friday evening, described as "an
encouraging sign" of Israel's decision to accept U.N. Security
Council Resolution 425 demanding the withdrawal of Israeli troops
from South Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Expressing concerns over the stalled Middle East peace process,
the two foreign ministers hoped all parties concerned to end
hostilities and abide by all signed agreements, and resume peace
talks.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed relations between the EU and Egypt, and
between Europe and the Mediterranean, and the latest developments
in the Gulf as well as the U.N. Security Council reform. 
</P>
</TEXT>
