<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Promote Hospital Health Care Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 5 (Xinhua) - Myanmar Health Minister
Major-General Ket Sein has stressed the need to strengthen health
laboratory services in hospitals to promote health care in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening of a seminar here Saturday, Ket Sein
said health laboratory services were crucial in surveillance,
diagnosis and prognosis in curative and preventive medicine and
public health care, the New Light of Myanmar newspaper reported
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He emphsized the need for achieving safe and quality blood and
transfusion free of HIV, hepatitis, malaria and VD viruses.
</P>
<P>
There were 726 hospitals in Myanmar in the 1996-97 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar laid down a five-year national health plan for
1996-2001. The plan includes six broad programs and 50 detailed
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
