<HEADLINE> Uruguayan Foreign Minister to Visit Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan Foreign Minister Didier
Opertti is scheduled to visit Peru on May 4 to boost trade
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day stay here, Opertti is also prepared to sign
some bilateral agreements, said Uruguayan Ambassador Diego Zorrila
San Martin, who did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
The top Uruguayan diplomat is to meet Peruvian President
Alberto Fujimori and hold talks with his Peruvian counterpart
Eduardo Ferrero Costa.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will discuss perspectives for economic
integration in the region and for a hemispheric free trade zone
covering North and South America. 
