<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Planes Collision Kill Five </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A private jet and single-engine
plane collided on Saturday in Georgia of the United States,
killing at least five people.
</P>
<P>
Both pilots and three passengers on the jet were killed, said
Preston Hicks, a spokesman with the National Transportation Safety
Board.
</P>
<P>
Although the jet's flight plan showed five people aboard, one
of the passengers never boarded the plane, The Associated Press
quoted Cobb County police spokesman Robert Quigley as saying.
</P>
<P>
The smaller plane did not file a flight plan.
</P>
<P>
Crews were searching for additional victims, but were hampered
by leaking jet fuel and twisted wreckage.
</P>
<P>
Quigley said the jet's pilot and three passengers were
co-workers from the Atlanta area.
</P>
<P>
The jet had just taken off from Peachtree-DeKalb County Airport
near Atlanta en route to Harrisburg, Pennsylvania, when it
collided with the smaller plane.
</P>
<P>
The planes hit the ground about a kilometer apart in a
subdivision of single-family homes. No one on the ground was
injured.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Aviation Administration and the National
Transportation Safety Board were on the scene investigating.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
