<HEADLINE> Germany Takes 3-0 Lead over South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Germany took an unbeatable 3-0 lead
over South Africa in their Davis Cup tennis World Group tie in
Bremen, Germany on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Veteran Boris Becker teammed up with David Prinosil to overcome
an one-set deficit before winning 5-7, 6-4, 6-4, 6-3 over David
Adams and Ellis Ferreira in the doubles rubber.
</P>
<P>
In the quarter-finals Germany will take on the winners of the
Sweden-Slovakia tie. Slovakia led the holders 2-1 after the
doubles on Saturday in Bratislava.
</P>
<P>
Becker, who replaced the injured Marc-Kevin Goellner, showed
glimpses of his form by blasting powerful serves.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, untested youngsters Nicolas Kiefer and Tommy Haas
defeated Grant Stafford and Wayne Ferreira respectively to put
Germany 2-0 ahead in Friday's two singles rubbers. 
</P>
