<DOCNO> XIE19980405.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Province Establishes Bottom Line Subsistence System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
has intensified efforts to introduce a bottom line subsistence
system for urban and rural residents.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government allocated 10 million yuan during 1997
to establish the system in both urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Some 136 counties, nearly 99 percent of the province's total,
and all its 14 prefectural cities have introduced the
system along with related rules and regulations covering
establishment and implementation procedures. Most of the people
benefitted from the system are those in remote and mountainous
areas, laid-off workers or old people without children to support
them.
</P>
<P>
Funding for the system comes from central and local financial
departments at various levels.
</P>
<P>
Related departments have distributed 15.67 million yuan
to help over 168,900 poverty-stricken people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
