<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 2000 GMT, April 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- At least three Palestinians were wounded in East
Jerusalem Saturday by Israeli soldiers as the Palestinians
continued protesting the murder of Hamas bomb maker Muhi Sharif.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of Palestinian youths held rally in the Abu Dis Arab
village in East Jerusalem to protest against the killing of
Sharif. (Palestine-Hamas-Protests)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair said here Saturday
that "a new era" has opened up in UK-China relations, and it is
good not only for the two countries, but also for Europe and the
rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
Blair said this at a joint conference with European Commission
President Jacques Santer, Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto and Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai after the
conclusion of the second Asia-Europe Meeting. (UK-EU-China)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Thousands of marchers walked the streets of
Memphis, Tennessee, of the United States Saturday on the 30th
anniversary of the assassination of Martin Luther King Jr.
</P>
<P>
The marchers followed a route much like the one the then
39-year-old civil rights leader led in his last march in Memphis a
week before he was gun down on April 4, 1968. (US-King-March)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The militant Palestinian group Islamic Resistance
Movement (Hamas), held a big rally in Gaza Saturday calling for
revenge attacks against Israel over the death of Hamas bomb maker
Muhi Sharif.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 pro-Hamas Palestinian students held an anti-Israeli
demonstration at the campus of Gaza's Islamic University and
later marched through central streets in central city.
(Palestine-Hamas-Revenge) 
</P>
