<P>
SHANGHAI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is currently hosting the
International Exposition on Polyurethane (PU), a new substitute
for chemical raw materials. The expo is the second one of this
kind held in China.
</P>
<P>
Some 80 raw materials manufacturers and processing equipment
suppliers from over 20 countries and regions are attending the
showcase event, including multinational firms such as BASF, ICI,
Bayer, Asahi Glass, and ACMOS Chemie.
</P>
<P>
PU is widely used in the aviation, automobile manufacturing,
household appliance, interior decoration, furniture, and footwear
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Beijing hosted the first exhibition on polyurethane in 1995,
and the third expo is expected to be held in Shanghai two or three
years later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
